{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":515,"text":"The universe is teeming with planets."},{"time":4118,"text":"I want us, in the next decade,"},{"time":5994,"text":"to build a space telescope that'll be able to image"},{"time":8387,"text":"an Earth about another star"},{"time":10488,"text":"and figure out whether it can harbor life."},{"time":13232,"text":"My colleagues at the NASA\nJet Propulsion Laboratory"},{"time":15392,"text":"at Princeton and I are working on technology"},{"time":18253,"text":"that will be able to do just that in the coming years."},{"time":21791,"text":"Astronomers now believe that every star"},{"time":23776,"text":"in the galaxy has a planet,"},{"time":25716,"text":"and they speculate that up to one fifth of them"},{"time":27992,"text":"have an Earth-like planet"},{"time":29068,"text":"that might be able to harbor life,"},{"time":30760,"text":"but we haven't seen any of them."},{"time":32522,"text":"We've only detected them indirectly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35260,"text":"This is NASA's famous picture of the pale blue dot."},{"time":38493,"text":"It was taken by the Voyager spacecraft in 1990,"},{"time":41290,"text":"when they turned it around as\nit was exiting the solar system"},{"time":44048,"text":"to take a picture of the Earth"},{"time":45760,"text":"from six billion kilometers away."},{"time":48082,"text":"I want to take that"},{"time":49650,"text":"of an Earth-like planet about another star."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52232,"text":"Why haven't we done that? Why is that hard?"},{"time":54632,"text":"Well to see, let's imagine we take"},{"time":56054,"text":"the Hubble Space Telescope"},{"time":58000,"text":"and we turn it around and we move it out"},{"time":59698,"text":"to the orbit of Mars."},{"time":61232,"text":"We'll see something like that,"},{"time":62440,"text":"a slightly blurry picture of the Earth,"},{"time":64508,"text":"because we're a fairly small telescope"},{"time":66829,"text":"out at the orbit of Mars."},{"time":68368,"text":"Now let's move ten times further away."},{"time":70384,"text":"Here we are at the orbit of Uranus."},{"time":72320,"text":"It's gotten smaller, it's got less detail, less resolve."},{"time":74806,"text":"We can still see the little moon,"},{"time":76591,"text":"but let's go ten times further away again."},{"time":78704,"text":"Here we are at the edge of the solar system,"},{"time":80435,"text":"out at the Kuiper Belt."},{"time":81733,"text":"Now it's not resolved at all."},{"time":83439,"text":"It's that pale blue dot of Carl Sagan's."},{"time":86103,"text":"But let's move yet again ten times further away."},{"time":88303,"text":"Here we are out at the Oort Cloud,"},{"time":89927,"text":"outside the solar system,"},{"time":91487,"text":"and we're starting to see the sun"},{"time":93103,"text":"move into the field of view"},{"time":94415,"text":"and get into where the planet is."},{"time":95879,"text":"One more time, ten times further away."},{"time":98010,"text":"Now we're at Alpha Centauri,"},{"time":99663,"text":"our nearest neighbor star,"},{"time":100903,"text":"and the planet is gone."},{"time":102252,"text":"All we're seeing is the big beaming image of the star"},{"time":104860,"text":"that's ten billion times brighter than the planet,"},{"time":107817,"text":"which should be in that little red circle."},{"time":109623,"text":"That's what we want to see. That's why it's hard."},{"time":111823,"text":"The light from the star is diffracting."},{"time":114143,"text":"It's scattering inside the telescope,"},{"time":115884,"text":"creating that very bright image"},{"time":117388,"text":"that washes out the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119140,"text":"So to see the planet,"},{"time":120411,"text":"we have to do something about all of that light."},{"time":122671,"text":"We have to get rid of it."},{"time":123902,"text":"I have a lot of colleagues working on"},{"time":125347,"text":"really amazing technologies to do that,"},{"time":127362,"text":"but I want to tell you about one today"},{"time":129177,"text":"that I think is the coolest,"},{"time":130674,"text":"and probably the most likely to get us an Earth"},{"time":132874,"text":"in the next decade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134410,"text":"It was first suggested by Lyman Spitzer,"},{"time":136482,"text":"the father of the space telescope, in 1962,"},{"time":139642,"text":"and he took his inspiration from an eclipse."},{"time":141758,"text":"You've all seen that. That's a solar eclipse."},{"time":143941,"text":"The moon has moved in front of the sun."},{"time":145981,"text":"It blocks out most of the light"},{"time":147741,"text":"so we can see that dim corona around it."},{"time":150117,"text":"It would be the same thing if I put my thumb up"},{"time":151780,"text":"and blocked that spotlight\nthat's getting right in my eye,"},{"time":154365,"text":"I can see you in the back row."},{"time":156277,"text":"Well, what's going on?"},{"time":157579,"text":"Well the moon"},{"time":159524,"text":"is casting a shadow down on the Earth."},{"time":161939,"text":"We put a telescope or a camera in that shadow,"},{"time":165174,"text":"we look back at the sun,"},{"time":166685,"text":"and most of the light's been removed"},{"time":168325,"text":"and we can see that dim, fine structure"},{"time":170415,"text":"in the corona."},{"time":171690,"text":"Spitzer's suggestion was we do this in space."},{"time":174357,"text":"We build a big screen, we fly it in space,"},{"time":177134,"text":"we put it up in front of the star,"},{"time":179181,"text":"we block out most of the light,"},{"time":180965,"text":"we fly a space telescope in\nthat shadow that's created,"},{"time":183981,"text":"and boom, we get to see planets."},{"time":185758,"text":"Well that would look something like this."},{"time":188421,"text":"So there's that big screen,"},{"time":190010,"text":"and there's no planets,"},{"time":190885,"text":"because unfortunately it doesn't\nactually work very well,"},{"time":193389,"text":"because the light waves of the light and waves"},{"time":196309,"text":"diffracts around that screen"},{"time":197989,"text":"the same way it did in the telescope."},{"time":199773,"text":"It's like water bending around a rock in a stream,"},{"time":202910,"text":"and all that light just destroys the shadow."},{"time":204700,"text":"It's a terrible shadow. And we can't see planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207373,"text":"But Spitzer actually knew the answer."},{"time":209140,"text":"If we can feather the edges, soften those edges"},{"time":211645,"text":"so we can control diffraction,"},{"time":213411,"text":"well then we can see a planet,"},{"time":215126,"text":"and in the last 10 years or so we've come up"},{"time":216925,"text":"with optimal solutions for doing that."},{"time":218969,"text":"It looks something like that."},{"time":222501,"text":"We call that our flower petal starshade."},{"time":224846,"text":"If we make the edges of those petals exactly right,"},{"time":227806,"text":"if we control their shape,"},{"time":229230,"text":"we can control diffraction,"},{"time":230788,"text":"and now we have a great shadow."},{"time":232234,"text":"It's about 10 billion times dimmer than it was before,"},{"time":234878,"text":"and we can see the planets beam out just like that."},{"time":238324,"text":"That, of course, has to be bigger than my thumb."},{"time":240182,"text":"That starshade is about"},{"time":241640,"text":"the size of half a football field"},{"time":243216,"text":"and it has to fly 50,000 kilometers\naway from the telescope"},{"time":246806,"text":"that has to be held right in its shadow,"},{"time":248866,"text":"and then we can see those planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":250830,"text":"This sounds formidable,"},{"time":252238,"text":"but brilliant engineers, colleagues of mine at JPL,"},{"time":255246,"text":"came up with a fabulous design for how to do that"},{"time":258126,"text":"and it looks like this."},{"time":259200,"text":"It starts wrapped around a hub."},{"time":260988,"text":"It separates from the telescope."},{"time":262967,"text":"The petals unfurl, they open up,"},{"time":265238,"text":"the telescope turns around."},{"time":266998,"text":"Then you'll see it flip and fly out"},{"time":269142,"text":"that 50,000 kilometers away from the telescope."},{"time":272357,"text":"It's going to move in front of the star"},{"time":274827,"text":"just like that, creates a wonderful shadow."},{"time":278110,"text":"Boom, we get planets orbiting about it."},{"time":281914,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":283638,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285997,"text":"That's not science fiction."},{"time":287950,"text":"We've been working on this\nfor the last five or six years."},{"time":290513,"text":"Last summer, we did a really cool test"},{"time":293116,"text":"out in California at Northrop Grumman."},{"time":295555,"text":"So those are four petals."},{"time":297138,"text":"This is a sub-scale star shade."},{"time":298850,"text":"It's about half the size of the one you just saw."},{"time":301347,"text":"You'll see the petals unfurl."},{"time":302807,"text":"Those four petals were built by four undergraduates"},{"time":304874,"text":"doing a summer internship at JPL."},{"time":307289,"text":"Now you're seeing it deploy."},{"time":308535,"text":"Those petals have to rotate into place."},{"time":310517,"text":"The base of those petals"},{"time":311687,"text":"has to go to the same place every time"},{"time":314060,"text":"to within a tenth of a millimeter."},{"time":315683,"text":"We ran this test 16 times,"},{"time":317443,"text":"and 16 times it went into the exact same place"},{"time":320282,"text":"to a tenth of a millimeter."},{"time":321723,"text":"This has to be done very precisely,"},{"time":323655,"text":"but if we can do this, if we can build this technology,"},{"time":326163,"text":"if we can get it into space,"},{"time":327647,"text":"you might see something like this."},{"time":329448,"text":"That's a picture of one our nearest neighbor stars"},{"time":331720,"text":"taken with the Hubble Space Telescope."},{"time":334314,"text":"If we can take a similar space telescope,"},{"time":336698,"text":"slightly larger,"},{"time":337956,"text":"put it out there,"},{"time":339378,"text":"fly an occulter in front of it,"},{"time":340764,"text":"what we might see is something like that --"},{"time":342954,"text":"that's a family portrait of our\nsolar system -- but not ours."},{"time":345890,"text":"We're hoping it'll be someone else's solar system"},{"time":348412,"text":"as seen through an occulter,"},{"time":350044,"text":"through a starshade like that."},{"time":351114,"text":"You can see Jupiter, you can see Saturn,"},{"time":353139,"text":"Uranus, Neptune, and right there in the center,"},{"time":355762,"text":"next to the residual light"},{"time":357102,"text":"is that pale blue dot. That's Earth."},{"time":359007,"text":"We want to see that, see if there's water,"},{"time":361381,"text":"oxygen, ozone,"},{"time":362786,"text":"the things that might tell us that it could harbor life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365309,"text":"I think this is the coolest possible science."},{"time":367718,"text":"That's why I got into doing this,"},{"time":369371,"text":"because I think that will change the world."},{"time":371341,"text":"That will change everything when we see that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373779,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":375365,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}